20/02/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Prime Minister Mirko Cvetkovic announced on Friday (February 18th) that a government reshuffle will take place by the end of the month with the merging of ministries.
He did not exclude replacing some ministers as well.
Cvetkovic also said that representatives of coalition partner G17 Plus will keep their seats in the reshuffled cabinet.
Three ministers from the party have left already.
On Monday, parliament is expected to confirm the resignations of Deputy Prime Minister and Economy Minister Mladjan Dinkic, Minister for the National Investment Plan Verica Kalanovic and Health Minister Tomica Milosavljevic.
(Beta, RTS, B92, Tanjug - 18/02/11)
